On ubuntu, you can do something similar with<p><pre><code>    upower -i /org/freedesktop/UPower/devices/battery_BAT1 | grep capacity | awk &#x27;{print $2}&#x27;
</code></pre>
You can see all of your power options with<p><pre><code>    upower -e</code></pre>

PHP : 1 week is not always 7 days:<p><pre><code>  $_1week = new DateInterval(&quot;P1W&quot;);
  $_7days = new DateInterval(&quot;P7D&quot;);
  var_dump($_1week == $_7days); // true
  var_dump($_1week);
  var_dump($_1week == $_7days); // false
  var_dump($_7days);
  var_dump($_1week == $_7days); // true
</code></pre>
<a href="http://3v4l.org/CcAk8" rel="nofollow">http://3v4l.org/CcAk8</a><p>Same result with &#x27;$_1week = new DateInterval(&quot;P7D&quot;);&#x27; :-)
